revert simply means rolling back changes after a successfull commit .
when reverting there are 2 types of statements are found.
1)revert with no conflict
  here you revert it for first time or you revert a different file for the first time.
  example done in merge-pull file
  commands used:- git revert <id>

2)revert with conflict 
  here you revert in same file so that to roll back some commits . but you face revert conflict issue ,
to solve that you use the same command but there is prompt saying "cant revert conflict issue".
check file for to keep which data in that particular file and exit
then continue with "git revert --continue" and "git add <file name>".


